JVM default encoding is ANSI in hyperledger/fabric-javaenv image. It causes that if we write code like following, the response will be "? ?" if val is a Unicode string such as "你好":
{code:java}
String val  = stub.getStringState(key);
if (val == null) {
    return newErrorResponse(String.format("Error: state for %s is null", key));
}
_logger.info(String.format("Query Response:\nName: %s, Amount: %s\n", key, val));
return newSuccessResponse(val, val.getBytes());{code}
 

Although it can be workaround as example code in fabric-sample, but it may be more easily to produce mistake. It also troublesome  for logging Unicode items.
{code:java}
return newSuccessResponse(val, ByteString.copyFrom(val, UTF_8).toByteArray());
{code}
 

Cloud we add some code in container entry point to set JVM default encoding to UTF-8 like this?
{code:java}
// in file: https://github.com/hyperledger/fabric-chaincode-java/blob/release-1.4/fabric-chaincode-docker/start#L67

exec "$JAVACMD" -Dfile.encoding=UTF-8 -jar $APP_HOME/chaincode/chaincode.jar "$@"
{code}

